'''[[libertarian]] [[socialism]]'''

# Any of a group of [[political]] [[philosophy|philosophies]] dedicated to opposing [[coercive]] forms of [[authority]] and social [[hierarchy]]: prominent examples being capitalism and the State; especially one that encourages the direct [[seizure]] by the people of the [[means of production]] with the aim of moving toward the creation of a radical direct [[democracy]].